Reference github:
https://github.com/lgozasht/TE-compartmentalization

Genomes:
Hydra 105: https://research.nhgri.nih.gov/hydra/jbrowse/jbrowse.cgi (GO file in functional annotation tab)
Hydra AEP: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/datasets/genome/GCF_038396675.1/  (GO file in FTP tab)
Hydractinia: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/datasets/genome/GCF_029227915.1/ (GO file in FTP tab)

Steps:
- open your conda environment
- module load miniconda/3.13
- conda activate env_name
- make a separate folder for each genome you're working with and go through this whole pipeline for one genome at a time
- download TE compartmentalization script from github into the folder you will be working with. Do everything in this folder
 - module load git/2.52.0
 - git clone https://github.com/lgozasht/TE-compartmentalization.git
 - delete "fi" on line 66 of TE-compartmentalization_pipeline.sh
 - nano TE-compartmentalization_pipeline.sh  then delete "fi" on line 66
 - cmmd+O, then cmmd+X to close
- download go-basic.obo file from this website: https://geneontology.org/docs/download-ontology/#go_basic
 - wget https://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/go/go-basic.obo
- copy repeatmasker library from another folder on the cluster to your folder
 - cp /software/apps/repeatmasker/gnu-4.1.5/Libraries/RepeatPeps.lib  RepeatPeps.lib
 - cp medusozoa_rep_lib to your folder and rename hydra_AEP-families.fa or hydra_105-families.fa (I have this file, need to give it to you)
 - mv medusozoa_rep_lib  hydra_AEP-families.fa
- Download genome data from genome links above and rename (look at paper github for more info):
- For AEP and Hydractinia:
 - module load ncbi/16.36.0
- click datasets and into command line
 - unzip dataset
- For Hydra 105:
- copy link addresses from Genome tab (hydra 2.0 genome assembly), Assembled transcripts (Juliano trinity transcripts), Protein models tab (hydra 2.0 protein model), and Gene models tab (hydra 2.0 gene models - this is the genomic.gff file for 105) rename files in format needed from paper's github (rna.fna -> transcripts.fa, protein.faa -> proteins.fa, GCF....hydra_aep.fna -> genome.fasta)
should have three files: genome.fa, transcripts.fa, proteins.fa
- convert genomic.gff or genomic.gff3 file to bed file with 6 columns and name it geneFile_final.tsv
- For AEP and Hydractinia
 - awk 'BEGIN{OFS="\t"} $3=="gene" {
  match($9, /ID=([^;]+)/, arr)
    print $1, $4-1, $5, arr[1], ".", "."
}' genomic.gff > geneFile_final.tsv
- For 105 (might have to rename genomic.gff in the script to what your .gff3 file is called):
 - awk 'BEGIN{OFS="\t"} /^#/{next} $3=="gene"{match($9,/Name=([^;]+)/,arr); print $1,$4-1,$5,arr[1],".","."}' genomic.gff > geneFile_final.tsv
- generate two files with code from step 5 of the github (from the file you just made)
 - cut -f 4 geneFile_final.tsv > all_genes.list_final.filtered
 - cut -f 4 geneFile_final.tsv > genes_with_terms_final.txt
- download GO annotation file from genome website
- For AEP and Hydractinia:
 - wget https://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/genomes/all/GCF/038/396/675/GCF_038396675.1_HydraT2T_AEP/GCF_038396675.1-RS_2024_06_gene_ontology.gaf.gz
 - gunzip filename (will be red)
- For 105
 - Functional annotations tab (Blast2go file)
 - wget blast2go_file_link
- reformat GO file to two columns
- make a file named GO_file_reformat.awk and paste the code below
 - BEGIN{OFS="\t"} /^!/ || /^#/ || /^DB/ {next} $3 != "" && $5 != "" { key = $3 SUBSEP $5 if (!(key in seen)) { seen[key] = 1 if ($3 in go_terms) { go_terms[$3] = go_terms[$3] ";" $5 } else { go_terms[$3] = $5 gene_order[++n] = $3 } } } END { for (i = 1; i <= n; i++) { g = gene_order[i] print g, go_terms[g] } }
- submit the script (change gofilename.gaf to your file name)
 - awk -f GO_file_reformat.awk gofilename.gaf > gene2GO_final.tsv
- should have a file named  gene2GO_final.tsv with two columns
- run this script to make a file with lengths of scaffolds (change genome fasta to name of your genome file (hydra_AEP.fna)
 - bioawk -c fastx '{print $name"\t"length($seq)}' genome.fasta | awk '$2>50000' > scaffolds.bed
- make a job script and submit code
- job submission info + modules needed + job script
 - module load miniconda/3.13
conda activate environment_name
module load repeatmodeler
sh TE-compartmentalization_pipeline.sh hydra_AEP genome.fasta RepeatPeps.lib go-basic.obo 90

